.TH SUTURE-LOG "1" "April 2026" "Suture v5.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
suture\-log \- Show commit history
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B suture log [\\fIoptions\\fR] [\\fIbranch\\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Show commit history.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \\\-g, \\\-\\\-graph
Show ASCII graph of branch topology
.TP
.BR \\\-\\\-first\-parent
Show only the first\-parent chain (skip merge parents)
.TP
.BR \\\-\\\-oneline
Show compact one\-line format
.TP
.BR \\\-\\\-author \\fI<author>\\fR
Filter by author name
.TP
.BR \\\-\\\-grep \\fI<pattern>\\fR
Filter by commit message pattern
.TP
.BR \\\-\\\-all
Show commits across all branches
.TP
.BR \\\-\\\-since \\fI<date>\\fR
Show commits newer than a date/time
.TP
.BR \\\-\\\-until \\fI<date>\\fR
Show commits older than a date/time
.TP
.BR \\\-\\\-stat
Show which files changed in each commit
.TP
.BR \\\-\\\-diff
Show patch content (diff) for each commit
.TP
.BR \\\-\\\-audit
Export structured audit trail (compliance format)
.TP
.BR \\\-\\\-audit\-format \\fI<format>\\fR
Output format for \-\-audit (json, csv, text)
.TP
.BR \\\-\\\-verify
Verify commit signatures
.TP
.BR \\\-\\\-diff\-filter \\fI<filter>\\fR
Filter by diff status: A (added), D (deleted), M (modified)
.TP
.BR \\\-\\\-limit \\fI<n>\\fR
Limit number of commits shown (default: 100, 0 = unlimited)
.TP
.BR \\\-C \\fI<REPO_PATH>\\fR
Run as if suture was started in <path>
.TP
.BR \\\-h, \\\-\\\-help
Print help
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
suture log                 # Show log for HEAD
suture log \\\-\\\-oneline       # Compact one\-line format
suture log \\\-\\\-graph         # ASCII graph of branch topology
suture log \\\-\\\-all           # Show commits across all branches
suture log \\\-\\\-author alice  # Filter by author
suture log \\\-\\\-grep "fix"   # Filter by message pattern
suture log \\\-\\\-audit         # Export structured audit trail
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR suture (1)
